The paper describes a software for drawing and analyzing causal diagrams, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of causal diagrams is particularly relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), where understanding causal relationships is important for developing accurate models. The software may also be relevant to social informatics (cs.SI), computer engineering (cs.CE), and systems and control (cs.SY), as these fields often involve analyzing complex systems with causal relationships.
